item.title: Footage shows Gaddafi's bloodied body
item.description: Footage obtained by Al Jazeera shows the body of the former Libyan leader Muammar Gaddafi following his death in Sirte.

item.title: Muammar Gaddafi killed in Sirte
item.description: NTC military chief says toppled leader died of wounds following capture near his hometown of Sirte.

item.title: Obituary: Muammar Gaddafi
item.description: One of the world's most eccentric and unpredictable leaders, Gaddafi dominated the world stage for decades.

item.title: Gaddafi as orator: a life in quotes
item.description: In speeches that at times stretched to several hours, Gaddafi's remarks astounded audiences in Libya and abroad.

item.title: Eccentricities of an enigmatic Gaddafi
item.description: From a fear of heights to a penchant for female bodyguards, Libya's ex-ruler betrayed fascinating traits.

item.title: Thai PM warns of Bangkok flooding

item.title: Greek strike resumes ahead of austerity vote
item.description: Second day of general strike gets under way with mass protests, as parliament takes final vote on new austerity laws.

item.title: Clinton urges Afghan reconciliation efforts
item.description: US secretary of state urges Kabul to keep up Taliban reconciliation efforts during visit to country.

item.title: Turkey continues attacks on Kurdish fighters
item.description: Funeral ceremonies held for 24 Turkish soldiers killed by PKK, as air force bombs group's bases in Iraq for second day.

item.title: Bolivian protesters arrive in La Paz
item.description: Nearly 2,000 indigenous Bolivians reach Andean capital after two-month march from their Amazonian homeland.
